istorical watershed before and after socialism as well as on a theoretical level by the sociology of knowledge. With its focus on Central and Eastern Europe this volume is an important contribution to the research on nonreligion and secularity.The collected volume deals with agents and media within specific cultural and historical contexts. Theoretical claims and conceptions by single agents and/or institutions in which the imparting of knowledge about religion and atheism was or is a central assignment, are analyzed. Additionally, procedures of transmitting knowledge about religion and atheism and of sustaining related institutionalized norms, interpretations, roles and practices are in the focus of interest.The book opens the perspective for the multidimensional and negotiating character of legitimation processes, being involved in the establishment or questioning of the institutionalized opposition between religion and atheism or religion and science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCommunicationxReligious aspects. 4aAtheismus. 4aReligionslosigkeit. 4aSozialismus. 4aSäkularität. 7aRELIGION / Atheism.2bisacsh  aNonreligion.  aatheism.  asecularity.  asocialism.1 aCoțofană, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleixner, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHafner, Johann Ev., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHazdovac Bajić, Nikolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolkunova, Ksenia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKołodziejska, Marta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarinović, Ankica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMöbius-Andre, Manuela, 